&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are a friendly Nutrition &amp; Dietetic team based at North Devon District Hospital in Barnstaple. We are looking for a motivated Advanced Practice Band 7 Paediatric Dietitian to work 37.5 hrs (5 days) per week, to lead our dietetic service provision to our Paediatric Diabetes Multi-disciplinary team, and to manage an in-patient and out-patient caseload across General Paediatrics, in liaison with the other Paediatric Dietitians. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post, you should have a relevant degree or equivalent qualification, be registered with the Health &amp; Care Professions Council as a Dietitian, and have significant post-registration clinical experience, and be able to demonstrate relevant professional development in Paediatric Dietetics, including Paediatric Diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will also be actively involved in supervising dietetic students on clinical placement from the University of Plymouth. We will help you develop further by supporting CPD activity and regular appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barnstaple is situated close to the fantastic surfing beaches of the North Devon coastline, and Exmoor national park. There is a good road link to the M5, and rail service to Exeter and the national network. For further information please contact Claire Morgan, Head of Nutrition &amp; Dietetics, on 01271 322306 or e-mail: ndht.dietetics@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this vacancy is offered at Band 7 subject to formal band matching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
